edu.illinois.library.cantaloupe.resolver

Interface Resolver

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FileResolver, StreamResolver

    public interface Resolver
    Locates and provides access to a source image. This is an abstract interface; implementations must implement at least one of the sub-interfaces.

    • Method Detail

      • getSourceFormat

        SourceFormat getSourceFormat(Identifier identifier)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Parameters:
        identifier -
        Returns:
        The expected source format of the image corresponding with the given identifier, or SourceFormat.UNKNOWN if unknown; never null.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if an image corresponding to the given identifier does not exist
        java.nio.file.AccessDeniedException - if an image corresponding to the given identifier is not readable
        java.io.IOException - if there is some other issue accessing the image
